# SCSS Reference

## Critical

```scss
// ❌ NEVER:
font-size: 18px; // raw px
@media (min-width: 768px) {
} // raw px in media query
@media (width < $md) {
} // desktop-first — NOT allowed in this project
@include bp-down() {
} // legacy helper
@include bp-up() {
} // legacy helper
font-size: 18px;
@media (width >= $md) {
	font-size: 22px;
} // don't use @media to change values — use fluid()

// ✅ ALWAYS:
gap: rem-calc(16); // Fixed values → rem-calc()
font-size: fluid(16, 24); // Responsive values → fluid(min, max)
@media (width >= $md) {
} // Mobile-first only — progressive enhancement for layout changes
```

## Media Query Rule (READ THIS)

This project uses two complementary tools for responsiveness:

1. **`fluid(min, max)` for _values_** — font sizes, spacing, padding, margins, gaps, radii. Never change these with `@media`.
2. **`@media` for _layout changes only_** — grid column count, flex direction, show/hide, position. Allowed when a layout genuinely restructures at a breakpoint, not as a way to tweak values.

**All `@media` queries MUST be mobile-first** (`width >= $bp`), not desktop-first (`width < $bp`). Write the mobile layout as the default, then progressively enhance for larger screens.

```scss
// ✅ GOOD — fluid() for values, mobile-first @media only for layout shape
.card-grid {
	display: grid;
	grid-template-columns: 1fr; // Mobile default
	gap: fluid(16, 32); // Value scales fluidly — no @media needed

	@media (width >= $md) {
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); // Layout change
	}

	@media (width >= $lg) {
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); // Layout change
	}
}

// ❌ BAD — desktop-first + @media used to change a value
.card-grid {
	grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); // desktop default
	gap: rem-calc(32);

	@media (width < $md) {
		// desktop-first direction forbidden
		grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		gap: rem-calc(16); // value change — should be fluid() instead
	}
}
```

**If the only thing changing at a breakpoint is a value (font-size, padding, gap, etc.), use `fluid()`, not `@media`.**

## Functions

```scss
rem-calc(16)              // → 1rem
fluid(16, 24)             // Responsive: 16px min, 24px max
fluid(16, 24, md, xl)     // Custom breakpoints
```

## Breakpoints

```scss
$sm: 576px;
$md: 768px;
$lg: 1024px;
$xl: 1200px;
$xxl: 1400px;
```

**No custom breakpoints.** You cannot add breakpoints of your own. Every `@media` query must use one of the breakpoints defined in `src/sass/partials/config/_breakpoints.scss` (`$xs`, `$ph`, `$sm`, `$md`, `$lg`, `$xl`, `$xxl`, `$xxxl`), and must reference the **variable name** — never the raw px value.

```scss
// ❌ NEVER:
@media (width >= 900px) {
} // raw px
@media (width >= 820px) {
} // unlisted breakpoint

// ✅ ALWAYS:
@media (width >= $md) {
} // use the variable from _breakpoints.scss
```

## Responsive Design

**Mobile-first approach** — write mobile styles as the default, then progressively enhance for larger screens using `@media (width >= $bp)`. Desktop-first `@media (width < $bp)` is **not allowed** in this project.

```scss
.component {
	// Mobile styles (default, unconditional)
	display: block;
	grid-template-columns: 1fr;
	gap: fluid(16, 24); // Value scales fluidly — no @media needed

	// Tablet+ — layout change only
	@media (width >= $md) {
		display: flex;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
	}

	// Desktop+ — layout change only
	@media (width >= $lg) {
		grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
	}
}
```

**Remember:** `@media` is for _layout changes_ (grid columns, flex direction, visibility), not _value changes_. Use `fluid()` for values that scale.

**Legacy exception:** A few pre-existing partials (`src/sass/partials/components/_header-menu.scss`, `src/sass/partials/mixins/_miscellaneous.scss` — the `swiper-cards-overflow-down` mixin) still use desktop-first `@media (width < $bp)` because rewriting them carries regression risk on live, shared UI. Mobile-first is **mandatory for all new code**, all block SCSS, and any partial you touch for unrelated reasons. Don't copy the legacy pattern into new work.

## Exceptions

1px borders, box shadows, values under 4px

## Config tokens — reuse first

Before writing any rule using a color, font, font-size, spacing, breakpoint, z-index, or easing value, check the config partials and reuse what already exists. If a new shared token is needed, add it to the matching config file rather than hardcoding inline.

**`src/sass/partials/config/_typography.scss`**

- Vars: `$serif-font-family`, `$sans-serif-font-family`, `$body-font-size`, `$body-font-family`, `$heading-font-family`, `$paragraph-line-height`, `$paragraph-margin-block-end`, `$heading-margin-block-end`
- Map: `$typography-styles` (h1–h6)
- Mixins: `@include font(h1..h6)`, `@include text(small|medium)`

**Headings → `h1`–`h6` class in markup, don't replicate heading typography in SCSS.** Tag follows semantics (document outline); class follows visual size. Applies to non-headings too when their typography matches a heading.

- Partial match → keep the class, override only the diff property. Don't rewrite from scratch.
- `.h1`–`.h6` classes set font properties only, **not** `color: $heading-color` (that's only on native `h1`–`h6` tags). On non-heading elements, add `color: $heading-color` explicitly if needed.
- No matching style → custom rule with `fluid()` + config tokens. Don't `@include font(...)` in block SCSS.

```html
<h2 class="h2">Same level</h2>
<h3 class="h2">Sized like h2, semantically h3</h3>
<span class="h1">Non-heading styled like h1</span>
```

**`src/sass/partials/config/_colors.scss`**

- Palette: `$pale`, `$mist`, `$sand`, `$muted`, `$deep`
- Semantic: `$primary-color`, `$secondary-color`, `$success-color`, `$info-color`, `$warning-color`
- Typography: `$body-color`, `$heading-color`, `$link-color`, `$link-hover-color`

**`src/sass/partials/config/_variables.scss`**

- `$container-padding-x`, `$menu-breakpoint`, `$custom-ease`
- Z-index scale: `$z-search`, `$z-header`, `$z-mobile-menu`, `$z-backdrop`, `$z-popup`
- Selection and scrollbar tokens

```scss
// ❌ NEVER:
.card {
	color: #080c11;
	font-family: 'Libre Baskerville', serif;
	font-size: 2rem;
}
// ✅ ALWAYS:
.card {
	color: $body-color;
}
// And in markup, use the heading class: <h2 class="h2">…</h2>
```

Always `@use` the partial in the consuming file rather than redeclaring values.

### When to add a new token vs. inline

Add to `_colors.scss` / `_typography.scss` / `_variables.scss` if:

- The value appears in **≥2 blocks** (or clearly will), OR
- It's a **brand or semantic concept** (brand color, section spacing step, z-index layer, easing curve), OR
- It's a value you keep re-deriving (a specific radius, a recurring border color)

Inline the raw value if it's a **one-off decorative value specific to this block** (e.g. a unique overlay opacity, a block-specific aspect ratio). When in doubt, prefer adding a token — hardcoded values drift faster than shared ones.

**Only swap a literal for a token when they're an exact match.** If the design value doesn't match any palette/config token (e.g. pure `#fff` when `$pale` is `#fbf8f3`, or pure `rgba(0, 0, 0, …)` when `$body-color` is `#080c11`), keep the literal — don't snap to the nearest token. Snapping silently shifts the design.

## VALUE vs LAYOUT Classification

Every responsive change is one of two kinds:

| Kind | Properties | Tool |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **VALUE** | `font-size`, `line-height`, `padding`, `margin`, `gap`, `border-radius`, fixed `inline-size` / `block-size` | `fluid(mobile, desktop)` |
| **LAYOUT** | `flex-direction`, `grid-template-columns`, `order`, `display` changes, `flex-wrap`, `position`, `max-inline-size: none → fixed` | Mobile-first `@media (width >= $bp)` |

Default to VALUE when unsure — prefer `fluid()` and keep media queries to a minimum. `max-inline-size: unconstrained → fixed` is always LAYOUT because `fluid()` cannot express "no constraint at mobile."

## Logical Properties

Always use logical CSS properties — never physical ones:

| ✅ Logical | ❌ Physical |
| --- | --- |
| `inline-size` | `width` |
| `block-size` | `height` |
| `margin-block-end` | `margin-bottom` |
| `padding-block` | `padding-top` + `padding-bottom` |
| `padding-inline` | `padding-left` + `padding-right` |
| `inset` | `top` / `right` / `bottom` / `left` |

Applies to all block SCSS and any new partials. Legacy partials that already use physical properties are exempt from forced rewrites.
